        "source": "autotrader",
        "url": "https://www.autotrader.com/cars-for-sale/vehicle/782067610",
        "whyGood": "NEW listing — 22,000 miles on a 2009 is extraordinary. The Saturn Sky uses the same Kappa platform as the Pontiac Solstice — a rear-wheel-drive roadster with a tight chassis and genuine sports-car intent. At 22K it's effectively new-condition with none of the wear. No Accidents. Premium trim adds leather and upgraded audio.",
        "whatToVerify": "Operate convertible top through full cycle (check motor and seals for any sitting-related stiffness). Inspect rubber weather seals for dry-rot from storage. Check tire age — 17-year-old tires at any mileage need replacement. Verify power steering fluid level and belts. Test A/C system. Look for any signs of long-term storage (mice damage, fuel system).",
        "bottomLine": "Unicorn condition car at top of budget — if it checks out mechanically, 22K miles on a fun RWD roadster is a once-in-a-decade find."
      },
      {
        "rank": 3,
